12/01/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry announced on Thursday (January11th) the departure of Ivan Chobanov, director of the national counterintelligence service, and Zhivko Zhivkov, chief commissioner of the gendarmerie.
After five years in office, Chobanov reportedly was offered the post of ambassador to Zimbabwe.
Zhivkov, however, was dismissed over alleged irregularities and misappropriations.
(24 Chasa, Sega, Dnevnik - 12/01/07;
Mediapool, bTV - 11/01/07)
